<subSubSection pageId="90" pageNumber="91" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="90.[150,1436,151,831]" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,736,760]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[327,472,736,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Japanagaliia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peculiaris">
<emphasis box="[327,472,736,760]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">J. peculiaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinctive in having a slightly asymmetrical aedegus and peculiar pygofer. It appears to resemble 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[378,480,772,795]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="javana">
<emphasis box="[378,480,772,795]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">J. javana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[533,645,772,795]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvata">
<emphasis box="[533,645,772,795]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="91">J. curvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be readily distinguished from them by the structure of the pygofer and aedeagus.
</paragraph>
